Changelog - current version 0.6.1

===========
Version 0.2
===========
Ability to look at surroundings (trees and pine trees).
New items (wands)
A couple of bug fixes.

===========
Version 0.3
===========
Lots more bug fixes.
Makefile editing.
Ability to look at monsters including details.
Monsters teleport less.
Ability to fight and kill monsters.
New font.
Waits for key release so that movement is more controlled.

===========
Version 0.4
===========
Ability to run (go) with the "g" key.
Automatically heal as you walk around.
Monsters should no longer teleport.
Some new graphics (white rat, crow).
View character stats.
Shows a message when you hit and kill monsters, and when 
they attack you.
More details when looking at monsters.
Resting can be interrupted by monster attacks.
Character skills (fighting) added, you get better the more you fight.
Monsters can poison you.
You die if your CHP is below zero (RIP image).
Returning to the splash screen starts a new game.
Looking is limited to your screen.
There is a small bug where there are a whole lot of monsters
(usually bunnies or rats) close together, sometimes they walk on
each other or on you.

===========
Version 0.5
===========
Fullscreen option, options menu.
Monsters can appear over the whole world now (bug fix).
You can hit or miss depending on +hit, +dam, fighting skill.
As you fight more your fighting skill goes up as do your +hit and +dam.
Monsters can also miss.
Code prettying up.
Can't run while you're poisoned (bug fix).
New monsters (griffin, goblin, worker ant, warrior ant, venus man trap,
              ent youth, albino bunny).
Loading screen (wait for it...)
Items on the field that you can pick up.
Hitting monsters makes them hostile, and they attack you.
Some monsters automatically attack you (green frogs and griffins).
After you attack a monster it becomes hostile.
Hostile monsters can only attack you on your screen or if less than 6 spaces away.
Much improved item images.
Monsters can walk on other corpses.
Going bugs fixed (Direction key doesn't press, doesn't say you hit the monster).
Ability to drop items that you don't want.
Inventory is set to default one when you begin a new game.
Certain monsters have "guardians" (ie Albino Bunnies, Warrior Ants)
Sound when you die, too.
Going stopped when you get near monsters, not just if you hit them.
 (so that you don't accidentally hit an Ent Youth.)

===========
Version 0.6 (Not released)
===========
New item, Bundle of Wood.
If Ent Youth or large monster walks through tree, it breaks it down.
You have levels and experience, monsters give experience.
You gain more hit points as you gain levels.
New monsters: Black widow, Black squirrel, Squirrel, Wolf Spider
Friendly monsters can't even hit you on accident (bunnies, squirrels)
Stop going automatically after entering a new screen.
New map tiles: Two new trees, tree stumps
Monsters are smarter and go around obstacles (such as other monsters).
 No more hiding behind Ent Youths and resting!
Menu is cleaner.
You can continue your game instead of starting a new one.
No longer start in the top left corner, starting place is random.
Town as well as forest. Kind of. 
New townspeople: Townsman, Townswoman, Urchin, Beggar, Drunkard, Town Guard
Town guard posted at each corner of the town.
Fixed bug where sometimes it doesn't say that you hit monsters.
Whole stat strings thing cleared up.
Ability to open and close doors.

=============
Version 0.6.1
=============
As we near the alpha release, versions will go up slower
The graphics are MUCH improved thanks to Dustin Miller.
All tiles are new.
Inn is a new building.
Tavern is a new building.
Houses are random sizes.
Path connects houses.
Walking into doors opens them (instead of having to press o).
Pressing Escape in the menu returns to the current game instead of quitting.
Dropping items works.
ItemClass created ... works well enough for now.
You identify more things when looking around.
When blind (never for now), you cannot identify what you are fighting.
Tons of code clean-up.
Going, closing and opening doors asks "Which direction?"
History shows the time.
Confirms hitting a friendly townsperson.
Attacking a friendly townsperson turns the town hostile against you.

=============
Version 0.6.2
=============
Sourceforge Project page:
  http://sourceforge.net/projects/nameofgame/
Easier to configure install.
More gradual scrolling of map allows you to see beyond the border.
This prevents you from accidentally running into a monster just over the border.
Returning to the town is possible! ;)
More efficient getdirection() method.
Fixed bugs: font '!' doesn't show up and looking cursor off-position.
New monsters: Townsman2, Townsman3, Townswoman2, Townswoman3, Veteran,
  Chicken, Pig.
MUCH smarter monsters. Not as much as I would wish yet but much improved over
  the previous version.
Some creatures run away from you if you are chaotic, and only attack if they
  are cornered.
Pressing Enter in the keypad centers the view of the map.
Prettier loading screen.
Fixed controls: ? (shift+slash) works to access help menu, shift+q now 
  returns to the main menu instead of just q, and shift+c accesses character
  stats instead of e.
You are able to view up to 23 lines of your history with shift+n.
Only working controls are shown in the Help menu.
